{"title":"Offensive item","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/Offensive_item","type":"markdown","data":"Any monster capable of wielding [weapons](/wiki/Weapon \"Weapon\") has a chance of being generated with a random **offensive item**, which might be an offensive [wand](/wiki/Wand \"Wand\"), [potion](/wiki/Potion \"Potion\") or [scroll](/wiki/Scroll \"Scroll\"). An eligible monster will be given an offensive item if its level equals or exceeds the roll of a *d75*.[\\[1\\]](#cite_note-1)\n\nThe following monster types are specifically ineligible for offensive items, even though they can wield weapons:\n\n- [Ettins](/wiki/Ettin \"Ettin\") (animal)\n- [Skeletons](/wiki/Skeleton \"Skeleton\") (mindless)\n- [Iron golems](/wiki/Iron_golem \"Iron golem\") (mindless)\n- [Keystone Kops](/wiki/Keystone_Kop_\\(monster_class\\) \"Keystone Kop (monster class)\") of any rank\n\nIf the [monster difficulty](/wiki/Monster_difficulty \"Monster difficulty\") is 8 or higher, there is a 1/35 chance that the item will be a [wand of death](/wiki/Wand_of_death \"Wand of death\"). Otherwise, a die is rolled according to the monster's difficulty:[\\[2\\]](#cite_note-2)\n\n| Difficulty | Roll  |\n| ---------- | ----- |\n| 3 or less  | *d8*  |\n| 4–6        | *d9*  |\n| 7 or more  | *d13* |\n\nThe result of this die roll is given by the following table:\n\n| Roll | Outcome                                                                         |\n| ---- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| 1    | [Scroll of earth](/wiki/Scroll_of_earth \"Scroll of earth\")[\\[3\\]](#cite_note-3) |\n| 2    | [Wand of striking](/wiki/Wand_of_striking \"Wand of striking\")                   |\n| 3    | [Potion of acid](/wiki/Potion_of_acid \"Potion of acid\")                         |\n| 4    | [Potion of confusion](/wiki/Potion_of_confusion \"Potion of confusion\")          |\n| 5    | [Potion of blindness](/wiki/Potion_of_blindness \"Potion of blindness\")          |\n| 6    | [Potion of sleeping](/wiki/Potion_of_sleeping \"Potion of sleeping\")             |\n| 7    | [Potion of paralysis](/wiki/Potion_of_paralysis \"Potion of paralysis\")          |\n| 8–9  | [Wand of magic missile](/wiki/Wand_of_magic_missile \"Wand of magic missile\")    |\n|      |                                                                                 |\n| 10   | [Wand of sleep](/wiki/Wand_of_sleep \"Wand of sleep\")                            |\n| 11   | [Wand of fire](/wiki/Wand_of_fire \"Wand of fire\")                               |\n| 12   | [Wand of cold](/wiki/Wand_of_cold \"Wand of cold\")                               |\n| 13   | [Wand of lightning](/wiki/Wand_of_lightning \"Wand of lightning\")                |\n\n## Use\n\nA user has suggested improving this page or section as follows:\n\n*\"Outline the circumstances under which a monster will make use of an offensive item.\"*\n\n## See also\n\n- [Death drop](/wiki/Death_drop \"Death drop\")\n- [Defensive item](/wiki/Defensive_item \"Defensive item\")\n- [Miscellaneous item](/wiki/Miscellaneous_item \"Miscellaneous item\")\n- [Monster starting inventory](/wiki/Monster_starting_inventory \"Monster starting inventory\")\n\n## References\n\n1. [↑](#cite_ref-1) [src/makemon.c in NetHack 3.6.6, line 556](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.6_Released/src/makemon.c#L556)\n2. [↑](#cite_ref-2) [src/muse.c in NetHack 3.6.6, line 1572](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.6_Released/src/muse.c#L1572)\n3. [↑](#cite_ref-3) If the monster would receive a scroll of earth, but is not wearing a metal helmet, a wand of striking will be given instead. A monster can also be protected from boulders by certain body types, but no weapon-wielding monster has any of these body types.\n\n[![This article has been updated to reflect NetHack 3.6.6. Click here for more information.](/images/5/57/Nh366-icon.png)](/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version \"This article has been updated to reflect NetHack 3.6.6. Click here for more information.\")\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Offensive item - NetHack Wiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Offensive_item\",\"wgTitle\":\"Offensive item\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":164412,\"wgRevisionId\":164412,\"wgArticleId\":11527,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"Todo\",\"Nethack-366 articles\",\"Monster Inventory\"],\"wgBreakFrames\":false,\"wgPageContentLanguage\":\"en\",\"wgPageContentModel\":\"wikitext\",\"wgSeparatorTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDigitTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDefaultDateFormat\":\"dmy\",\"wgMonthNames\":[\"\",\"January\",\"February\",\"March\",\"April\",\"May\",\"June\",\"July\",\"August\",\"September\",\"October\",\"November\",\"December\"],\"wgMonthNamesShort\":[\"\",\"Jan\",\"Feb\",\"Mar\",\"Apr\",\"May\",\"Jun\",\"Jul\",\"Aug\",\"Sep\",\"Oct\",\"Nov\",\"Dec\"],\"wgRelevantPageName\":\"Offensive_item\",\"wgRelevantArticleId\":11527,\"wgRequestId\":\"beaff456c247f6ad6d18d266\",\"wgCSPNonce\":false,\"wgIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRelevantPageIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRestrictionEdit\":[],\"wgRestrictionMove\":[],\"wgWikiEditorEnabledModules\":[],\"wgCategoryTreePageCategoryOptions\":\"{\\\"mode\\\":0,\\\"hideprefix\\\":20,\\\"showcount\\\":true,\\\"namespaces\\\":false}\"});mw.loader.state({\"site.styles\":\"ready\",\"noscript\":\"ready\",\"user.styles\":\"ready\",\"user\":\"ready\",\"user.options\":\"ready\",\"user.tokens\":\"loading\",\"ext.cite.styles\":\"ready\",\"mediawiki.legacy.shared\":\"ready\